qas.question: What is the vowel system of Catalan?
How many stressed phonemes are there in Catalan?
What language form differs in the amount of vowel reduction?

context: Catalan has inherited the typical vowel system of <a0_0>Vulgar Latin<a0_0/>, with <a1_0>seven<a1_0/> stressed phonemes: /a ɛ e i ɔ o u/, a common feature in <a2_0>Western Romance<a2_0/>, except <a3_0>Spanish<a3_0/>. Balearic has also instances of stressed /ə/. <a4_0>Dialects<a4_0/> differ in the different degrees of vowel reduction, and the incidence of the pair /ɛ e/.
